@page
@model ComprehensiveNavigation.Pages.Docs.GettingStartedModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Getting Started";
    Layout = "_DocsLayout";
}

<div>
    <p>This guide helps you understand how the project is structured to offer robust routing.</p>
    
    <h4>Key Concepts Demonstrated</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Endpoint Routing:</strong> Default folder-based routing matches Razor Pages.</li>
        <li><strong>Route Parameters:</strong> Used in Product Details (<code>@@page "{id:int}"</code>).</li>
        <li><strong>View Components:</strong> Encapsulate logic for Menus, Breadcrumbs, and Sidebars.</li>
        <li><strong>Programmatic Redirects:</strong> Encountered in the Admin Dashboard.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr class="my-4" />
    
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
        <a asp-page="/Docs/Index" class="btn btn-outline-secondary">&larr; Overview</a>
        <a asp-page="/Docs/Installation" class="btn btn-primary">Next: Installation &rarr;</a>
    </div>
</div>
